cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DB, cs.HC, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on security and privacy in e-health systems, and analyses a protocol for the same. This makes cs.CR the most likely sub-category. 
2. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper also discusses the societal implications of privacy breaches in e-health systems, which could fall under cs.CY. 
3. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper deals with the storage and management of sensitive health data, which could be relevant to cs.DB. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses the privacy concerns of users in e-health systems, which could be relevant to cs.HC. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes suggestions for fixing ambiguities in the e-health protocol, which could be relevant to cs.SE.
